Nordic dance duo anamē and Danish singer-songwriter Lydmor collaborate on ‘Peaceful Avenues’, out now on Anjunabeats. 

The collaborative work of Marcus Schössow and Thomas Sagstad reached its latest apex last year with their debut album ‘Beautiful World’, a record that the pair have envisioned since first meeting over two decades ago. Following on from solo work with the likes of Swedish House Mafia, Axwell /\ Ingrosso and Kaskade over the last ten years, the duo’s debut album is the latest milestone in their expansive discographies. 

Originally featured as part of ‘Beautiful World’, ‘Peaceful Avenues’ is renowned as one of the biggest moments in anamē’s set lists. Now, the anthemic track now sees its own release alongside multiple new mixes. 

'Peaceful Avenues’ (Unplugged) sees Lydmor deliver a slow and emotional rendition of the popular track from a grand piano in Above & Beyond's studio. Also included in the release are a shorter edit of the original, as well as a full piano 'Unplugged' Instrumental Mix. Fans can expect to see behind-the-scenes footage of the recording process to be posted on anamē and Lydmor’s social and YouTube channels in the coming weeks. 

anamē are currently on their worldwide Beautiful World Tour with upcoming shows in the USA, Canada, Hong Kong, Europe and more for any fans looking to see 'Peaceful Avenues' played out live in a city near them. Tickets on sale now (www.anamemusic.com/tour).

Progressive house duo ANUQRAM remix Above & Beyond's 'Crazy Love’ (feat. Zoë Johnston), out now on Anjunabeats.

The latest offering from GRAMMY-nominated artists Above & Beyond and Zoë Johnston is ‘Crazy Love’, an uplifting and ethereal trance record first debuted to 20,000 fans at the trio’s Group Therapy 500 celebration in Los Angeles in 2022, and went on to become an instant classic. Road tested at Above & Beyond shows such as Red Rocks in Colorado, EDC Las Vegas, and Printworks in London, the track soon became a mainstay in their sets and a highly-sought after ID. Now, progressive house duo ANUQRAM drop their own rework of the smash hit. 

ANUQRAM have come a long way since their 2021 Anjunabeats debut, ‘Echoes’ (with PROFF). With a sonic signature of their own, they’ve earned support from the likes of Armin van Buuren, Vintage Culture, David Guetta, Oliver Heldens, Cosmic Gate, Farius and beyond. They kicked off this year with their ‘On My Knees EP’, which saw spins from Solarstone, Ferry Corsten, Cosmic Gate, Harry Diamond, Farius, Tritonal and more.

Last year, Above & Beyond achieved RIAA Gold-certification on the track, ‘Don’t Leave’, from 2019 ambient album 'Flow State', and were the only British DJs to sell out two consecutive nights at Printworks as part of the iconic London venue’s closing season. They also returned to Red Rocks Amphitheatre to helm two shows alongside label stars from Anjunabeats and Anjunadeep, and made an appearance at Insomniac's Escape Halloween festival in California.

GRAMMY-nominated singer and songwriter Zoë Johnston first collaborated with Above & Beyond on 2004’s ’No One On Earth’. She’s since co-written and featured on every Above & Beyond dance and acoustic studio album, which includes beloved hits like ‘Good For Me’, ‘You Got To Go’, 'Love Is Not Enough', ‘We’re All We Need’ and ‘Reverie’.

The accomplished British vocalist has also written and recorded songs with the likes of Faithless, Bent and Delirium, and racked up over 12 million combined streams across her catalogue in 2023 alone.

Above & Beyond's next live celebrations will take place at the Drumsheds in London, headlining the Radio 1 Dance event, followed by shows at 900 Marin St in San Francisco and SeatGeek Stadium in Chicago. The trio will also return to headline their Group Therapy 600 celebrations in Mexico City on October 19. Tickets on sale now at www.aboveandbeyond.nu/tour. 

'Crazy Love' (ANUQRAM Remix) is out now on Anjunabeats.
